ETPush Class Reference

Inherits from NSObject
Declared in ETPush.h

Overview

This is the main interface to the Salesforce MobilePush SDK. It is meant to handle a lot of the heavy lifting with regards to sending data back to Salesforce.

Please note that this is a singleton object, and you should reference it as [ETPush pushManager].

Configuring the app for ETPush

ETPush.h

– configureSDKWithAppID:andAccessToken:withAnalytics:andLocationServices:andProximityServices:andCloudPages:withPIAnalytics:error:

This is the main configuration method, responsible for setting credentials needed to communicate with Salesforce. If you are unsure of your accessToken or environment, please visit Code@ExactTarget

- (BOOL)configureSDKWithAppID:(NSString *)etAppID andAccessToken:(NSString *)accessToken withAnalytics:(BOOL)analyticsState andLocationServices:(BOOL)locState andProximityServices:(BOOL)proximityState andCloudPages:(BOOL)cpState withPIAnalytics:(BOOL)pIAnalyticsState error:(NSError **)configureError

Parameters

etAppID

The App ID generated by Code@ExactTarget to identify the consumer app
accessToken

The designed token given to you by Code@ExactTarget that allows you access to the API
analyticsState

Whether or not to send analytic data back to Salesforce
locState

Whether or not to use Location Services
proximityState

Whether or not to use Proximity Services. Using proximity services requires setting locState to YES
cpState

Whether or not to use Cloud Pages
pIAnalyticsState

Whether or not to send Web and Mobile analytic data back to Salesforce
configureError

NSError object describing the error

Return Value

Returns YES if successful or NO if failed. Do not proceed if NO is returned

Discussion

This is the main configuration method, responsible for setting credentials needed to communicate with Salesforce. If you are unsure of your accessToken or environment, please visit Code@ExactTarget

Each of the flags in the method are used to control various aspects of the MobilePush SDK. The act as global on/off switches, meaning that if you disable one here, it is off eveywhere.

– updateET

Triggers an immediate send of Registration data to Salesforce Marketing Cloud and will wait 60 seconds to send for all calls made after the first call was made while the app is in foreground.

- (void)updateET

Discussion

Triggers an immediate send of Registration data to Salesforce Marketing Cloud and will wait 60 seconds to send for all calls made after the first call was made while the app is in foreground.

This is not normally needed as each method (setTag(), setSubscriberKey(), addAttribute() etc) will trigger a send to the SFMC 60 seconds after the first request to change any Registration data.

A one-shot method to get notification up and running in your app.

Parameters

delegate

From Apple: “To guarantee that your app is able to respond to actionable notifications, you must set the delegate before your app finishes launching. A set of UNNotificationCategory objects for push notifications. These may be modified after registration via setUserNotificationCenterCategories.

ETPush.h

– shouldDisplayAlertViewIfPushReceived:

Tell the SDK to display a UIAlertView if a push is received while the app is already running. Default behavior is set to NO.

- (void)shouldDisplayAlertViewIfPushReceived:(BOOL)desiredState

Parameters

desiredState

YES/NO if you want to display an alert view while the app is running.

Discussion

Tell the SDK to display a UIAlertView if a push is received while the app is already running. Default behavior is set to NO.

Please note that all push notifications received by the application will be processed, but iOS will not present an alert to the user if the app is running when the alert is received. If you set this value to true (YES), then the SDK will generate and present the alert for you. It will not play a sound, though.

ETPush.h

– addAttributeNamed:value:

Adds an attribute to the data set sent to Salesforce.

- (BOOL)addAttributeNamed:(NSString *)name value:(NSString *)value

Parameters

name

The name of the attribute you wish to send. This will be the key of the pair.
value

The value to set for the data pair.

Return Value

YES if added successfully

Discussion

Adds an attribute to the data set sent to Salesforce.

The Attribute Name cannot be nil or blank, or one of the reserved words.

Will trim leading and trailing whitespace from the name and value.

The attribute must be defined within the SFMC Contact model prior to adding a value. If the attribute does not exist within the SFMC Contact model, then this attribute will be accepted by the SDK, but will be ignored within the SFMC.

If you previously added a value for the named attribute, then the value will be updated with the new value and sent to the SFMC.

If you send in a blank value, then the value will be sent to the SFMC to remove that value from the Contact record.

All attribute values set with this method persist through the installation of the app on your customer device.

Note that attribute mapping is case sensitive, and spaces should be avoided when setting up new attributes in the SFMC Contact model.

ETPush.h

+ isPushEnabled

Returns whether this device can receive Push Notifications.

+ (BOOL)isPushEnabled

Discussion

Returns whether this device can receive Push Notifications.

Push is considered enabled if the application is able to present an alert (banner, alert, sound) to the user. If UIUserNotificationTypeNone (ios8+) or UIRemoteNotificationTypeNone (iOS7) is true, then Push is disabled and this method returns false. For iOS8+, isRegisteredForRemoteNotifications must also return true.

ETPush.h

+ setLoggerWithHandler:

To override the logging that the SDK does with your own logging code. Adding this logging handler will replace the logs that the SDK prints to the console.

+ (void)setLoggerWithHandler:(void ( ^ __nullable ) ( NSString *))customLogger

Parameters

customLogger
  • A completion handler that will be called each time the SDK logs to the console. Instead of calling NSLog to log to the console, the SDK will call this customLogger and provide the String that was going to be logged.

Discussion

To override the logging that the SDK does with your own logging code. Adding this logging handler will replace the logs that the SDK prints to the console.

Typical uses would be to save the logs in your own logging datastore instead of printing to the console.

NOTE: Do not base any program logic on the contents of the String received as a parameter as we do not guarantee the contents of a log string will remain the same from one release to another.

– refreshWithFetchCompletionHandler:

Ask ETPush to update its data. ETPush will throttle attempts based on the time since the last time this was called.

- (BOOL)refreshWithFetchCompletionHandler:(void ( ^ __nullable ) ( UIBackgroundFetchResult result ))completionHandler

Parameters

completionHandler

The UIBackgroundFetchResult completion handler. This method will be called with UIBackgroundFetchResultNoData if no attempt was made to update data, otherwise it will be called with UIBackgroundFetchResultNewData after the update completes. If nil is passed, then process of the completion handler must be managed by the caller.

Return Value

True if ETPush did make an attempt at updating data

Discussion

Ask ETPush to update its data. ETPush will throttle attempts based on the time since the last time this was called.
